      description: 'Gather a collection of mismatched socks in various colors, patterns, and sizes, or print illustrated sock pairs. Children find matching pairs, count the total number of pairs, and record their results. Extend the activity with math challenges: if you have eight socks, how many pairs is that, or if three pairs are striped and two pairs are spotted, how many socks do you have in total. This hands-on activity connects clothing themes to counting by twos, multiplication readiness, and addition.',
